-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-J&J, Nimble Storage, UnitedHealth Group 
-- 
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 04:00AM EDT
-- None



April 16 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Nimble Storage, UnitedHealth Group and Xoom, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Nimble Storage <NMBL.N>: Raymond James starts with a market perform rating  * UnitedHealth Group <UNH.N>: Citigroup cuts to neutral from buy rating * Xoom Corp <XOOM.O>: Evercore raises to equal-weight from underweight rating   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Comcast <CMCSA.O>: ISI Group raises price target to $60 from $59; rating buy * Comerica <CMA.N>: Jefferies cuts price target to $48 from $49; rating hold * Comverse <CNSI.O>: Oppenheimer cuts price target to $36 from $44; rating outperform * Conocophillips <COP.N>: Oppenheimer raises price target to $85 from $80; rating outperform * Halcon Resources <HK.N>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to $4.75 from $4; rating hold * Hhgregg Inc <HGG.N>: Jefferies cuts price target to $8 from $9; rating hold * J&J <JNJ.N>: Credit Suisse raises price target to $100 from $94; rating underperform  * Nimble Storage <NMBL.N>: Raymond James starts with a market perform rating   * Northern Trust <NTRS.O>: Jefferies cuts price target to $64 from $66; rating hold * Synovus Financial <SNV.N>: Suntrust Robinson raises to buy from neutral   * UnitedHealth Group <UNH.N>: Citigroup cuts to neutral from buy rating